title: How’s the Stock Market? Depends on Whose Room You Visit

title: Nouriel Roubini Sees A Bad Recovery And A Depression
text: During the last crisis, the economist Nouriel Roubini earned the nickname "Dr. Doom" for his ominous prognostications about the economy and financial system. While he prefers the moniker "Dr. Realist" Roubini is once again extremely negative. On this week’s episode he explains why he sees a poor recovery, then a bout of inflation, and then ultimately a depression in the wake of this crisis.

title: Europe to enter ‘recession of historic proportions’ amid coronavirus
text: The coronavirus pandemic is plunging the European Union into a recession, the European Commission said Wednesday in its spring economic forecast.
